Short code defined like this
&amp;lt;a data-flickr-embed=&amp;#34;true&amp;#34; data-header=&amp;#34;true&amp;#34; data-footer=&amp;#34;true&amp;#34; href=&amp;#34;{{ index .Params 1 }}&amp;#34; title=&amp;#34;{{ index .Params 0 }}&amp;#34;&amp;gt; &amp;lt;img src=&amp;#34;{{ index .Params 2 }}&amp;#34; width=&amp;#34;800&amp;#34; height=&amp;#34;600&amp;#34; alt=&amp;#34;{{ index .Params 0 }}&amp;#34;&amp;gt; &amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;script async src=&amp;#34;//embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js&amp;#34; charset=&amp;#34;utf-8&amp;#34;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt; First parameter is the album title. Second parameter is the album URL. Third parameter is a URL to an image to use for the album.</description></item><item><title>Inktober 2020 Album</title><link>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/ink2020_01/</link><pubDate>Fri, 02 Oct 2020 09:27:36 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/ink2020_01/</guid><description>Inktober 2020 Flickr Album All my drawings from Inktober 2020</description></item><item><title>Hornsea 2020</title><link>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/hornsea/</link><pubDate>Tue, 22 Sep 2020 11:03:37 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/hornsea/</guid><description>Photos from recent trip to Hornsea.
Hornsea Museum Sign Hornsea Beach Hornsea Beach Stones Betty the beach dog</description></item><item><title>Acorn Electron Sound Mod</title><link>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/acornmod/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Aug 2020 08:31:48 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/acornmod/</guid><description>Interest video about modding the Acorn Electron.</description></item><item><title>Flickr shortcode</title><link>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/flickrshort/</link><pubDate>Tue, 18 Aug 2020 11:39:52 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/flickrshort/</guid><description>Yellow Flowers Testing a Flickr shortcode I found here flickr-hugo-embed and tweaked for my own needs.</description></item><item><title>Hugo Lbry Shortcode</title><link>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/lbry_shortcode/</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Aug 2020 13:50:32 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://blog.0x32.co.uk/posts/lbry_shortcode/</guid><description>One thing I like about Hugo is how easy it is to expand its functionality with your own code.
For example was able to create a shortcode to embed Lbry.tv videos into a post in around five minutes.
First I created an empty file layouts/shortcodes/lbry.html which I pasted the basic embed code take from the share button on one of their videos.
&amp;lt;iframe id=&amp;#34;lbry-iframe&amp;#34; width=&amp;#34;560&amp;#34; height=&amp;#34;315&amp;#34; src=&amp;#34;https://lbry.tv/$/embed/this-new-fedora-powered-thinkpad-p53-is/097106eb68aebc90b33d83bb053467af942a8e20&amp;#34; allowfullscreen&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/iframe&amp;gt; Then parameterized this so that the src url can be changed.</description></item></channel></rss>